SchwartzSet

Class FirstMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.IntWritable,VertexArrayWritable>
      • SchwartzSet.FirstMap

  • public class FirstMap
extends org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.IntWritable,VertexArrayWritable>
    This is the Map Method for the first Mapreduce Round of the computation of the Schwartzset. The strict dominance matrix is read from the input files and the datastructure needed for the following computation is created.
    The input files contain the strict dominance matrix by row (each file contains one or more rows).
    The first entry in each line of the inputfile is the row number and is read as InputKey of type Text.
    The InputValue (the remaining characters in the line) is the corresponding row of the adjacency matrix of the dominance graph.

    The (key,value)-pairs created by this method have keys of type IntWritable and values of type VertexArrayWritable.
